    <pw:title>
      The Most Dangerous of Devotions
    </pw:title>
    <pw:file-name>
      the_most_dangerous_of_devotions
    </pw:file-name>
    <pw:body>
      <p>
        The most dangerous of devotions, in my opinion, is the one endemic to Christianity: <i>I was not born to be of this world.</i> With a second life waiting, suffering can be endured -- especially in other people. The natural environment can be used up. Enemies of the faith can be savaged and suicidal martyrdom praised. 
      </p>
